<font color="#FF0000">WANNABES</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb 17 14:00:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Wannabes - people who wish they had or could.  Havebeens - those that served, experienced and survived.  To all you Havebeens, take a positive view the of the others, they envy you and covet your experiences. I think you should take pride in what you did and be flattered that there are Wannabes out there wanting to emulate you.  Hopefully there is sorrow and regret from a nation of people that grew up all to suddenly, there should be some respect and recompense to a generation that did their obligation.    I should like to say &quot;Well Done&quot; to those who went and came back without any recognition.  Thank you to all those who gave the ultimate.
<p><code>-- robert.hart@uk.sun.com  (Robert Hart USN 1961-1969) </code><p>


